have trouble distinguishing different vowels in English. Obviously, the difficulty one has in learning how to speak language depends on a lot of factors, but I do wonder if in general, languages with larger vowel (and similarly, consonant) inventories tend to be perceived as more difficult to learn.%0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://phoible.org/inventories/view/2176%0a%3c https://phoible.org/inventories/view/2196%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
